                            <comment id="17084911" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 16 Apr 2020 14:29:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hmm that options is part of various HTTP components like jetty, undertow, servlet from Camel. But I guess platform-http is a different kind when none of those from Camel are in use.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17084912" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 16 Apr 2020 14:30:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The parameter btw is used for allowing HTTP OPTIONS verb or not (default off)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17084976" author="ppalaga" created="Thu, 16 Apr 2020 15:17:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The PR &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/camel/pull/3752&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/camel/pull/3752&lt;/a&gt; is fixing the immediate issue reported here, but it does not solve the problem that the platform-http component offers no real support for CORS beyond enabling the OPTIONS method handling. Plz file a separate issue for that, if necessary.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
